$$
\left[\begin{array}{l}
\pi\left(x^{2}-x+1\right)=\pi(x-1)+2 \pi k \\
\pi\left(x^{2}-x+1\right)=\pi-(x-1) \pi+2 \pi n
\end{array}(k, n \in \mathbb{Z})\right.
