{ x ^ { 2 } = 2 n + 1 }
\end{array} \Longleftrightarrow \left[\begin{array}{l}
x=1 \pm \sqrt{2 k-1} \\
x= \pm \sqrt{2 n+1}
\end{array}\right.\right.\right.
$$

If $0 \leq 1 \pm \sqrt{2 k-1} \leq 2$, then $-1 \leq \pm \sqrt{2 k-1} \leq 1 \Leftrightarrow 0 \leq 2 k-1 \leq 1 \Leftrightarrow k=1$, then $x=0$ or $x=2$. If $0 \leq \sqrt{2 n+1} \leq 2$, then $0 \leq 2 n+1 \leq 4 \Leftrightarrow n=0$ or $n=1$; then $x=1$ or $x=\sqrt{3}$. Answer: $0+1+2+\sqrt{3}$.

