For \(n \geq 2\) it holds that

\[
2^{2^{n}}=2^{4 \cdot 2^{n-2}}=16^{2^{n-2}}
\]

Since every power of 16 ends with 6, the last digit of \(2^{2^{n}}\) for \(n \geq 2\) is always 6, and consequently, the last digit of \(2^{2^{n}}+1\) is 7.
